3.00	Hatley_Park	Hatley Park National Historic Site	Hatley Park National Historic Site is located in Colwood, British Columbia in Greater Victoria. It is the site of Hatley Castle, a Classified Federal Heritage Building. Since 1995, the mansion and estate have been used for the public Royal Roads University. From the 1940s-1995, it was used for the Royal Roads Military College, a naval training facility.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Hatley_Castle.jpg/250px-Hatley_Castle.jpg
